        <li><strong>Switch Rear Power Disconnect to OFF:</strong> Locate the power disconnect switch on the rear of the console chassis. Rotate or toggle to OFF position. Verify the position is stable.</li>
        <li><strong>Disconnect AC Mains Power Cord:</strong> Fully remove the AC power cord from the mains outlet (wall, UPS, or power strip). Store the cord safely away from the work area.</li>
        <li><strong>Wait Minimum 5 Minutes:</strong> Allow 5 minutes for internal capacitors to discharge and thermal components (especially Heater FRU) to cool. Do not proceed before this wait period expires.</li>
        <li><strong>Verify Absence of Residual Hazards:</strong> Visually inspect the chassis for any signs of equipment damage or fluid leakage. Use a non-contact infrared thermometer to verify Heater FRU surface temperature is safe to touch (&lt;40°C).</li>
